## Payload Length Encoding

| Payload Length | Encoding |
|----------------|----------|
| 0-125 | 1 byte (direct) |
| 126-65535 | 1 byte (126) + 2 bytes (big-endian) |
| 65536+ | 1 byte (127) + 8 bytes (big-endian) |

## Control Frame Constraints

Per RFC 6455:
- Control frames (Close, Ping, Pong) cannot be fragmented
- Control frame payload max 125 bytes
- Control frames can appear between fragments

## Error Cases

- Payload exceeds max_payload_size
- Invalid opcode
- RSV bits set without extension
- Unmasked frame from client
- Masked frame from server (optional, some servers accept)
- Control frame fragmented
- Control frame payload > 125 bytes

